snippet.textDisplay:
This song is so beautiful specially because of the little girl Tanishka who sings the mukhda. Her voice has all the innocence and sweetness of a pure soul. It's not just a song it's a story of a beautiful family. Very well scripted and executed by talented Sachin and Jigar 
Rekha ji's flawless voice is like the holy Ganga, sacred and it sounds like the voice is blessing you :) 
Kirtidan Gadhvi 's strong voice gives that secured feeling to the daughter. Such beautiful Melody. The shehnai, manjeera, Sarangi, xylophone and every other instrument so beautifully arranged. I am in love with this whole composition. So Indian.. So colorful. God bless you all and our Indian music
snippet.textOriginal:
